Context: http://tour.golang.org/methods/8

The example showing how to check for err being nil always shows the converted integer; the converted integer should only be shown if there is no error? Suggested code:

```
i, err := strconv.Atoi("42")
if err != nil {
    fmt.Printf("couldn't convert number: %v\n", err)
} else {
    fmt.Println("Converted integer:", i)
}
```
